#Approach:

Find Missing and Repeating Number – Math Equations Approach

Is problem me array me 1 se n tak ke numbers hone chahiye,
lekin ek number repeat ho raha hai aur ek number missing hai.

Maan lo:
x = repeating number
y = missing number

Hum expected sum aur expected square sum nikalte hain for numbers 1 to n.

Actual array ka sum aur square sum bhi nikalte hain.

Phir:
actual sum - expected sum = x - y

Aur:
actual square sum - expected square sum = x² - y²

Hume pata hai:
x² - y² = (x - y)(x + y)

To isse x + y nikal sakte hain.

Ab hamare paas do equations aa gayi:
x - y
x + y

In dono ko solve karke repeating number x aur missing number y nikal lete hain.

Is approach me array modify nahi hota aur answer direct math se mil jata hai.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(1)

#Code:

class Solution {
    public int[] findMissingRepeatingNumbers(int[] nums) {
        int n = nums.length;
        long S = 0;
        long S2 = 0;

        long Sn = (long)n * (n + 1) / 2;
        long S2n = (long)n * (n + 1) * (2L * n + 1) / 6;

        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++){
            S += nums[i];
            S2 += (long)nums[i] * nums[i];
        }

        long val1 = S - Sn;      // x - y
        long val2 = S2 - S2n;    // x^2 - y^2
        val2 = val2 / val1;      // x + y

        long x = (val1 + val2) / 2;  // repeating
        long y = x - val1;           // missing

        return new int[]{(int)x, (int)y};
    }
}
